# Instinct RPG — Player Primer

The **live** player-facing primer is `instinct-rpg-primer-v2.html`, embedded in Card Studio via the
**Player Primer** tab (`index.html` → iframe). Older `instinct-rpg-primer*.html` files are not live
unless Annie explicitly switches the iframe.

## Audience & scope (teach-the-table)

- **Goal:** get first-time players to the table — not full rules mastery.
- **GM defers:** Contests, Snap Check procedure, Threat, Resolve — mention + glossary tap; GM teaches
  at the table when they arise. Do not expand into full procedures unless Annie asks.
- **In scope:** deck/hand philosophy, basic checks (Build/Roll/Read), Hit Dice intro, card types at a
  glance, how a card plays, 21-card chargen flow, keyword glossary, playtest FAQ.
- **Locked rhetoric:** deck = character; hand = Instincts right now; partial control / freestyling;
  Crit = natural 6; Flourish = gain bonus options from the card (don't "give up" 6s); pacing when
  hands run low (~2 average).

## Card samples

- Mount Baserow HTML from `card-data.js` via the `MOUNTS` map in the primer script — one sample per
  chargen step. Do not hand-paste stale card HTML.
- When adding a new card type to chargen samples, pick a **current** `Card_Key` from `card-data.js`
  and verify render in-browser.

## Render parity (`primer-card-scope.css`)

Primer loads `primer-card-scope.css` + `instinct-dual-styles.css` — **not** Card Studio's full
`index.html` card CSS. Every card HTML template used in samples must have scoped styles here:

| Template | Body class | Notes |
|----------|------------|--------|
| Ability / React / Act | `.cbody` | `.flv`, `.etxt`, `.csec` |
| Bond / Instinct / B&A forks | `.bf-body` | dual-path fork CSS in `instinct-dual-styles.css` |
| Core | `.card-body` | `.zone-label`, `.effect-text`, `.rule` — **required**; Core cards break without them |

- Fixed card frame: `2.5in × 3.5in`, scaled `.cardwrap` at `0.58` — **one card per** `.primer-cards`
  slot. For side-by-side Core samples, wrap each in its own `.primer-cards` inside `.primer-core-pair`.
- `padding-bottom: 26px` on body regions clears absolutely positioned `.idtag`.

## Typography

- **Serif** (`Crimson Pro`): section narrative paragraphs and golden-rule quotes.
- **Sans-serif** (`system-ui` stack): sub-topic labels only — `.step-sub-title`, `.ex-step-num`,
  `.chargen-label`. Do not switch detail/body paragraphs to sans without Annie explicitly asking.

## Tone & FAQ

- Playtest FAQ: welcoming, non-confrontational. Hand-first framing ("look at what surfaced") over
  policing player intent.
- Glossary: keyword only in `<summary>` — no subtitle stems/hooks after the term.
- Walkthrough example should use **named fiction** (e.g. Barbarian **Break** + ally **Aid**) and show
  how pool size is built (2d6 base + Aid = 3d6).

## Ship checklist

After primer edits: commit + push `main` (see `instinct-git.mdc`). No Baserow push unless card HTML
changed. Share the live link:
